{"questionId":"15423","questionHtml":"<p>In order to estimate the amount of oxygen consumed, this regression line is considered to be reliable for a temperature <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> such that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span> ≤ <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> ≤ <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>Write down the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span> and of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a = 10\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>10</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; <strong>AND&nbsp;</strong> <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b = 30\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>30</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em><strong><em>(A1)</em><em>&nbsp; (C2)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept [10, 30] or 10&nbsp;≤ <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> ≤ 30.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"15423","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ2.T_2c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"In order to estimate the amount of oxygen consumed, this regression line is considered to be reliable for a temperature x such that a ≤ x ≤ b . Write down the value of a and of b .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailabl